        Healthy Recipes\n\n1.
        Fruit Salad \nA mix of fresh fruits like bananas, apples and oranges.\n\n2.
        Grilled Chicken \nLow-fat grilled chicken served with vegetables.\n\n3.
        Vegetable Stir fry\nCarrots, broccoli and pepper cooked lightly.\n\n4.
        Oatmeal Breakfast\nOats with milk and fruits.\n\n5.
        Avocado Toast\nWhole grain bread topped with avocado.\n\n6.
        Boiled Eggs\nRich in protein and easy to prepare.\n\n7.
        Smoothie Bowl\nBlended fruits with yoghurt and nuts.\n\n8.
        Brown Rice and Beans\nHealthy and full of fiber.\n\n9.
        Baked Fish\nFish baked with lemon and spices.\n\n10.
        Greek Yoghurt with Honey\nGood for digestion and very nutritious.
    </string><string name="nutrition_advice_content">
        Advice:\n\n1.
        Hydration first — Drink plenty of water, unsweetened tea, or black coffee. Limit sugary drinks and alcohol.\n\n2.
        Build balanced meals — Include protein + fiber-rich veggies + healthy fat for satiety.\n\n3.
        Limit added sugars — Keep under 10% of daily calories (ideally much less). Avoid sugary beverages entirely.\n\n4.
        Read labels — Watch for hidden sugars, sodium, and ultra-processed ingredients.\n\n5.
        Meal prep smartly — Batch-cook proteins and veggies. Keep healthy snacks (nuts, fruit, yogurt) accessible.\n\n6.
        Eat mindfully — Pay attention to hunger/fullness cues. Enjoy meals without distractions when possible.\n\n7.
        Stay active — Pair nutrition with movement (150+ minutes moderate activity per week for adults).\n
